  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_non_primary_cancer">Non Primary Cancer</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_malignant_abnormality">MALIGNANT ABNORMALITY</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
If cancer 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cell">CELLS</xref>
 spread from the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_primary_cancer">Primary Cancer</xref>
 to another part of the body, the new area of cancer is called a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_non_primary_cancer">Non Primary Cancer</xref>
, 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_non_primary_cancer">Secondary Cancer or Metastasis</xref>
.  </p>

